data.text:
Summary

MK40 4TN is a residential postcode in Great Denham, Bedford. It was first introduced in November 2016.

The most common council tax bands are E and C.

Residential buildings are typically terraced (including end-terrace) and detached. Domestic properties are mostly houses and flats.

Estimated residential property values, based on historical transactions and adjusted for inflation, range from £1,944 to £1,749,807 with an average of £428,300.

Most residential buildings are of unknown age.

Domestic properties are predominantly owner occupied.

The most common Energy Performance Certificate (EPC) rating is B.

MK40 4TN is in the Bedford travel to work area. NHS services are provided by the Bedfordshire Primary Care Trust.
